			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				ok gang. Here is the deal. It doesn't matter what class you play, you are going to be USELESS at some point, at some time , in some zone, on some raid, in some group....<BR>
Necros are easily one of the best and most powerful in the game. Non one argues that, now all of a sudden, its the 'death of necros' and all. If you ever played Dungeons and Dragons, which is where all role playing fantasy games base from, you know that there are times when a single person can't do it all. Hence, the GROUP atmosphere which is required to make anything really fun, rewarding or challenging worthwhile. You think you are useless in a raid because you can't do your horrendous 1000+ point dots on a mob? Get over it. You wanna play a useless character? Try any melee class without a healer of some kind. &quot;Excuse me, can I bum a heal?&quot; &quot;Excuse me, can I bum a heal?&quot; &quot;Excuse me sir/ma'am, I haven't bothered you yet, can I bum a heal?&quot; Your alternative? Sit and recover hit points at at the slowest rate possible, yes, even slower than recovering mana. In short, ANY char will have times when things aren't the 'perfect' scenario you like to play in. Adapt, overcome, invent new ways to make the people in your group say &quot;wow, that was awesome how you did so and so.&quot;<BR>
I have a 50 necro a 45+ pally and a 26 monk, and no one can tell me that the price necros pay in a raid, IF their job happens to change a little bit is too high. My necro levelled like a madman, as did all my necro friends, as did all of you who have necros because quiet simply, we could. You guys ever look and see how MANY of us there are? How many people Verant is trying to keep happy at one time? Take a look, and yes you may think you can do better, but remember you have all day to think up ways to make things better, they have minutes here and there, moments between trying to make the game better for ALL of us by creating new zones, splitting servers when they become overcrowded and the like. You aren't happy with your character in a raid, don't take him, roll up whatever class you think is cool that day and go for it. Who is always selling the best equipment in Ecommons? Necros. Who is always soloing something it would take a group to kill? Necros. Who has the spell effects of almost every class combined into thier books AND get a kick ass tank to hide behind? Necros. Stop whining, everyone is tired of hearing about poor little necros.
				</font>
